
[1]opobalsam

   OPOBAL'SAM, n. [L. Gr. juice, and balsamum.]

   The balm or balsam of Gilead. It has a yellowish or greenish yellow
   color, a warm bitterish aromatic taste, and an acidulous fragrant
   smell. It is held in esteem as a medicine and as an odoriferous unguent
   and cosmetic. The shrub or tree producing this balsam is of the genus
   Amyris, and grows spontaneously in Arabia Felix.
